OL,3,C'Showstopper' peacock voted Britain's
OL,4,Cfavourite butterfly
OL,6,FMs Merry added: "Taking part in the
OL,7,FBig Butterfly Count couldn't be
OL,8,Feasier, simply spend 15 minutes in any
OL,9,Foutdoor space and count the
OL,10,Fbutterflies and day-flying moths you
OL,11,Fsee and submit your sightings to help
OL,12,Fbuild our interactive map.
OL,14,F"This information will help
OL,15,Fconservationists to see how some of
OL,16,Four more-common species are faring,
OL,17,Fwhich in turn helps to build a wider
OL,18,Fpicture of how all butterflies and
OL,19,Fmoths are doing."
